[#TheHedgehogAtHome] Wish you could smell the butter and almond aromas when my Prune Muffins/ Cake just came out from my airfryer!😍
.
Was inspired by @The.Italian.Hob's fresh pear cake, so here's my version. I like how this recipe uses almond flour and it came in really handy as my (normal) flour supply is now running low. Have been checking out my supermarket's baking section for the last few weeks, but flour and yeast have run out. It's crazy. No prizes for guessing what everyone's doing at home during this period. 🤣 Swipe ⬅️ for more pics.

@healthy_tadkaa I used airfryer. 160 degrees celcius. For the first 30 min, cover with aluminium foil. Thereafter, remove the foil and continue baking for another 5 to 10 minutes till golden brown. Enjoy and let me know how it turns out! 😄
Prune and muffins seem to be a killer combo 😍
Wish I could grab some now! Hahaha
@sugarcoatedwithlove Thank you Cecilia! Yeah this is the bigger airfryer. 👍
Wow, looks so good. Your airfryer is big! 😍👍
Woah the airfryer sure can do wonders 😋👍
@lovehasnotimelimitnboundaries Haha! Just using whatever I can find in the house! 😆
Yum! I think prunes are very underrated
@imafoodaddictx Hee hee, okay! I'll get ready a Tupperware container for you ❤️
